column1: For every Emergency Department encounter, hospitals (licensed by the California Department of Public Health) may report a Principal External Cause of Morbidity and up to 4 Other External Causes of Morbidities.  The External Cause Code Frequency Report shows the frequency of the reporting of each code.
ExtCauseCode = the external cause of morbidity, according to ICD-10-CM.
ExtCauseDesc = the description of the external cause of morbidity code.
ICD-10-CM (International Classification of Diseases, 10th Revision, Clinical Modification), effective for encounters beginning October 1, 2015.
TotalExtCauseCodes = the total number of times the E-Code was reported in any position.
PrimaryExtCauseCodes = the total number of times the External Cause Code was reported as a Principal External Cause of Morbidity.
SecondExtCauseCodes = the total number of times the External Cause Code was reported as a Secondary External Cause of Morbidity.
Data Source: California Emergency Department Data, Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development
